abstract: The candidate keeps talking about winning “unwinnable fights.” But the New Hampshire primary was not supposed to be in that category.
snippet: The candidate keeps talking about winning “unwinnable fights.” But the New Hampshire primary was not supposed to be in that category.
lead_paragraph: CONCORD, N.H. — Two days before a once-mission-critical primary in a state she neighbors, Senator Elizabeth Warren — typically exceptional at holding a room — had not finished speaking when something unusual happened: Dozens of voters began filtering out of the middle school gym she had reserved.

abstract: With the possibility of five leading candidates surviving beyond New Hampshire, the prospect of a long contest looms large.
snippet: With the possibility of five leading candidates surviving beyond New Hampshire, the prospect of a long contest looms large.
lead_paragraph: EXETER, N.H. — The Democratic presidential candidates amplified their attacks on one another on Monday in the final hours before polls open in New Hampshire, highlighting the deep divisions between the party’s left and center even as their campaigns prepared for a set of even more pivotal contests in the weeks ahead.

abstract: After Joe Biden’s fourth-place finish in Iowa, some supporters fear that a damaging result in Tuesday’s primary could hurt his financial resources to compete in later contests.
snippet: After Joe Biden’s fourth-place finish in Iowa, some supporters fear that a damaging result in Tuesday’s primary could hurt his financial resources to compete in later contests.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — His donors and supporters around the country are uneasy. His poll numbers in New Hampshire and nationally look increasingly shaky. He faces intense competition for moderate Democratic support and uncertainty about his viability in future contests.

abstract: The Dart Container Corporation, which makes foam products, is a manufacturing behemoth and produced a fortune for the family behind it. Environmentalists say its products are polluting the globe.

abstract: The investor Chamath Palihapitiya urged start-ups and venture capitalists to reconsider where they get their money from, in light of a new report on a Mormon Church mega-fund.

abstract: If your preferred candidate doesn’t win the nomination, will you still do everything you can to deny Trump a second term?
snippet: If your preferred candidate doesn’t win the nomination, will you still do everything you can to deny Trump a second term?
lead_paragraph: It’s been a rough week for Democrats. President Trump is preening over his acquittal, his poll numbers and the economy, while the Democratic nomination race looks like a divided mess. Many Democratic voters are anxious that they have no great candidates, only those guaranteed to alienate one half of the party or the other.

abstract: Hosted by RuPaul and featuring Justin Bieber as musical guest, this week’s show also had another memorable Oscar segment.
snippet: Hosted by RuPaul and featuring Justin Bieber as musical guest, this week’s show also had another memorable Oscar segment.
lead_paragraph: It was a week in which President Trump was acquitted in his impeachment trial in the Senate and gave his annual State of the Union address, and the results of the Democratic caucuses in Iowa descended into chaos, delays and recrimination. So, naturally, “Saturday Night Live” began with … a parody of the Democratic debate in New Hampshire.
